---
description: >
  Convert between sudoers file formats. It is shipped as part of the sudo
  package, installed by default on virtually every Linux distribution.
functions:
  file-read:
    - description: >
        When given a non-sudoers file as input, `cvtsudoers` attempts to
        parse it and prints each line as part of a syntax error message,
        effectively disclosing the full file contents.
      code: |
        LFILE=/path/to/file
        cvtsudoers "$LFILE" 2>&1
  sudo:
    - description: Read files with elevated privileges.
      code: |
        LFILE=/path/to/file
        sudo cvtsudoers "$LFILE" 2>&1
---
